news.title: Women’s participation can play key role in beautification of India's Smart Cities: Minister
news.para: D Thara, additional secretary, Union Ministry of Housing & Urban Affairs emphasized on the need for looking beyond developing the buildings and housing complexes and aim for integrated infrastructure management in order to achieve a sustainable habitat.

news.title: Wakefit Innovations files draft papers with Sebi; seeks to raise ₹468 crore via fresh issue
news.para: The proposed IPO of the Bengaluru-based company is a combination of a fresh issue of equity shares aggregating up to Rs 468.2 crore and an offer for sale (OFS) of 5.84 crore equity shares by the selling shareholders, according to the draft red herring prospectus (DRHP) filed on Thursday.

news.title: Sobha to invest ₹800 crore in residential project in Greater Noida
news.para: The project spread over 3.46 acres and have a total development potential of approximately 9.3 lakh sq ft.

news.title: Randeep Hooda buys an apartment worth ₹5.63 crore in Mumbai
news.para: Randeep Hooda's apartment has a built-up area of 142.19 sq meter (1,530 sq ft). The transaction was registered in June 2025.

news.title: Slums in Bhopal's central area to shift
news.para: Information suggests that nine slum settlements situated near Vallabh Bhawan will be shifted to Banganga, near Jinsi and other locations where estimated 14,000 permanent residences will be built through a Public-Private Partnership (PPP) arrangement.

news.title: Delay in tax recovery from merged areas hampers Pune civic body's revenue generation
news.para: The state govt has put a cap on charging "maximum of twice the property tax compared to what the residents were paying when they were under gram panchayat" but the nitty-gritty of the implementation has not been worked out by the state govt, claimed PMC.

news.title: Structural study of Margao’s unsafe buildings finally begins
news.para: Acting on direct orders from South Goa collector Egna Cleetus, a team from Goa College of Engineering (GEC) conducted inspections of four buildings earlier this week.

news.title: Jaiprakash Associates' promoters file petition in SC over land cancellation in Noida
news.para: However, the court refused to grant any interim stay or relief on the plea filed on June 7. Instead, it issued notice and directed the current SLP be tagged with the already pending related case.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM opens portal for property services in Ghaziabad
news.para: ​The portal provides digital access to over 1.40 lakh people, enabling them to pay property dues, download documents, manage instalment accounts, book registries, and change names with just a single click of a button from home.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespaces to redevelop Mulund West project worth ₹1,250 crore
news.para: The project spans across a 3.08-acre land parcel and has an estimated development value of approximately ₹1,250 crore.

news.title: FIR in illegal sand mining in Hirehalla River filed without names in Koppal
news.para: The joint operation with the taluk sand monitoring committee led to the seizure of 3,000 metric tonnes of sand valued at Rs 2.4 lakh and over 50 boats on June 20. The BJP, however, dismissed the FIR as baseless and considered it a mere procedural formality.

news.title: Karur collector to file plan on illegal sand mining: State to Madras HC
news.para: The court was hearing suo motu proceedings initiated to prevent illegal sand mining in the Amaravathi riverbed, following a petition filed by the registrar (judicial) of the Madurai bench.

news.title: Arrest Dreamz Infra India's MD for delay in delivery, refusing refund: NCDRC
news.para: The commission had earlier issued a bailable warrant against Disha Choudhury, the managing director of company Dreamz Infra India Ltd for not complying with its order to appear before it. Left with no option, a bench of Justice Inderjit Singh and Sadhna Shanker directed her arrest.

news.title: Fifteen farmhouses built in protected Aravalis razed after NGT order in Gurugram
news.para: The demolition — following directions of National Green Tribunal (NGT) to get rid of all illegal structures in areas that are under Aravali Notification — was carried out by municipal council of Sohna.

news.title: About 100 buyers get registries at RG Luxury Homes in special camps in Noida
news.para: The camp, held at the project site in Greater Noida West, marked the beginning of the registration process. Authorities have been instructed to organise similar camps in other legacy projects to expedite the handover process.

news.title: Tiruvallur administration seeks more time to clear 194 houses from lake in Avadi
news.para: The collector's report was filed in response to earlier NGT directions in Aug 2024 and March 2025, when the tribunal took stock of encroachments identified and notices issued to 350 individuals under the Tamil Nadu Protection of Tanks and Eviction of Encroachment Act, 2007.

news.title: Punjab rejigs conversion policy, industrial plots can be used to build hotels, office space
news.para: Renewable energy minister Aman Arora said, "Industrial plots of 1,000 square to 4,000 square yards can now be used for commercial activity, banquet halls, rental housing, office space or housing, institutes, or industrial workers' housing, depending on various categories and the width of roads. It will give relief to developers and investors in the state."

news.title: Blackstone buys $2 billion of CRE loans from Atlantic Union Bankshares
news.para: The loans were bought at a slight discount to their face value, the companies said on Thursday. The loans originated from Sandy Spring Bank, which Atlantic Union bought in a $1.6 billion deal in April.

news.title: Gujarat CM announces uniform house tax of ₹200 annually for PMAY-Gramin beneficiaries
news.para: An annual house tax assessment rate of Rs 200 has been fixed for four years, starting from the current assessment cycle, for houses constructed with government assistance within the limits of all Gram Panchayats across the state, according to the release.
